•
The impact of changes in economic conditions and the global capital markets, including those resulting from geopolitical events, adverse equity market conditions, volatility in the financial markets and evolving investment trends;
•
The effects on us from competition and financial and budgetary pressures affecting our clients;
•
Failure to successfully develop new and enhanced products and services;
•
The impact of our global presence and operations and any expansion and our exposure to additional issues from our increased global footprint;
•
Failure to comply with laws, rules or regulations; changes to current laws, rules or regulations; or the introduction of new laws, rules or regulations relevant to our business;
•
Inability to protect our intellectual property rights;
•
The impact of foreign currency exchange rate fluctuation;
•
The impact of our indebtedness on our cash flows and financial flexibility;
•
The impact of changes in our credit ratings;
•
Our exposure to tax liabilities in various jurisdictions; and
•
Failure to attract, develop or retain talent.
